VIRAT KOHLI
Born on November 5, 1988, in Delhi, he's a top-order batsman and former all-format captain for India.
He is widely considered one of the greatest batsmen in cricket history, nicknamed the "Chase Master" for his ODI run-chasing ability.
Kohli led India to many victories and was a highly successful captain across Tests, ODIs, and T20Is.
He holds numerous records, including being the fastest to reach several ODI run milestones (10k, 12k, 13k).
He is the leading run-scorer in the Indian Premier League (IPL) and has scored over 80 international centuries.
Kohli won the ICC Cricketer of the Year award in 2017 and 2018.
He's known for his intense passion, fitness, and aggressive on-field demeanor.
He made his international debut in 2008.
